Change the toString() method signature in the solution to 'public String toString()' (keep the @Override annotation) and ensure the method returns a String. Example:

@Override
public String toString() {
    return "Lecture{" +
           "lectureName='" + lectureName + '\'' +
           ", numberOfInscribedStudents=" + numberOfInscribedStudents +
           ", numberOfGuestStudents=" + numberOfGuestStudents +
           ", numberOfLecturers=" + numberOfLecturers +
           ", numberOfTutors=" + numberOfTutors +
           '}';
}

This aligns the solution with the problem specification and fixes the compile/override error.
